      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The continuum mechanics model employs J2 isotropic hardening plasticity for Ti-6Al-4V ELI, calibrated against uniaxial coupon data (N=6 specimens). Augmented Lagrangian frictional contact (μ=0.25 ± 0.05) is used at the screw-block interface; sensitivity to friction coefficient was assessed in the Sobol analysis. Linear kinematics are appropriate for the pre-yield stiffness QoI; large-deformation formulation (updated Lagrangian) is activated for post-yield force-displacement. Model form uncertainty estimated at 8.1 N/mm (stiffness) via ensemble spread across three independently constructed models. Gradation 4: physics basis documented, model-form uncertainty quantified via ensemble, constitutive law calibrated to material data.",
