      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly correspond to the regulatory submission metrics for ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance. Stiffness governs implant-spine load sharing; yield force is the primary failure threshold; force at 40 mm characterizes post-yield energy absorption relevant to surgical revision risk. The mapping from QoIs to clinical decision consequence (revision surgery risk) is documented in the clinical rationale section of the submission package. Gradation 4: QoIs are explicitly mapped to regulatory and clinical endpoints with documented justification.",
